               *******************************************
               ** The Immortal Rules of Rivers of Blood **
               *******************************************
 
1)  Do not kill mortals, do not kill mortals, do not kill mortals.
    This includes transferring/summoning them to aggressive mobs.
 
2)  Do not cheat for ANY mortal in ANY way, especially your own. 
    Unless of course you LIKE deletion. Yes this includes tanking,
    healing/restoring, casting protection spells <armor, sanct>,    
    and softening up or altering mobs.
 
3)  Do not transfer or summon mobs to mortals or mortals to mobs.
    They have legs, if they want to kill a mob, they can easilly
    go there themselves.
 
4)  DO NOT kill the shopkeepers for any reason at ALL.
 
5)  DO NOT use reboot.  <--- Note, simple English.
 
6)  Do not give out free equipment.  You don't need to win brownie
    points with the mortals.  Quest are fine but handing out items
    isn't.
 
7)  A note on quests: Quests are a good thing, more or less, BUT 
    do not give out overly extravagant prizes.  Exercise some 
    common sense here folks.  Do not load items more than 4 levels
    below their normal level (i.e. no level 5 ogre gauntlets).
 
8)  Do not undermine the authority of a higher level god.  If you 
    see that someone has been frozen or nochannelled do not restore
    their privileges.  They are being punished for a reason.  Any
    god that is higher than you has more authority than you, so if
    they ask you a question, you MUST answer... if it's something 
    illegal but the lower is following orders, the higher level one 
    is the one who gets in trouble.     
 
9)  Do not try to overrule each other. (unless there is a level difference,
    then the higher imm's decision is the one that takes precedence)
 
10) Trusted mortals:  Do not use your god powers to help your mortal
    character.  If you do, your trust will be taken away.

11) Do not powertrip.  Period.

12) Do not tell or let any mortal know who your mortals are.  They should 
be secret at all times.

13) Do not snoop anyone if you don't have a good reason to (ie VERY good 
evidence that they're cheating, or if they specifically ask you to) The 
mortals have a right to privacy if they are doing nothing wrong.

14) If someone is breaking a rule, your course of action is to FIRST 
trans them to you to talk.  You MUST be visible to them.  Tell them that 
what they are doing is wrong, and ask them to refrain.  If it merits a 
punishment make sure the punishment fits the crime.  But tell them BEFORE 
you punish them what they did wrong, why it is wrong, and what the 
punishment is.  If they have any complaints about your discretion, advise 
them to talk to one of the IMPS, and put the punishment on hold if possible.

15) If your mortal is directly involved in a conflict with someone and 
you think the other person should be punished, it is NOT up to you to log 
your imm on to resolve it.  Write a note, WITH YOUR MORTAL, tell the 
other person you are writing a note, and leave it for an imm (or 
preferably an imp) who wasn't involved handle it.

16) After punishing someone for something, write a note to immortal 
stating what you did, why you did it, and what the outcome and 
circumstances are.  Under no circumstances may you punish someone and not 
leave a note.

17) Anything you hear or learn about as an immortal is NOT for mortal 
ears.  If you learned it on the immortal channel, or through imm 
commands, do not tell any mortal what it is.  This includes ANYBODY's 
multis. 

18) If you are a guild leader, your guild must roleplay the part.  It is 
up to the guild leader to make sure that they do so.

19) All imms must log on at least once a week.  If you are going to be 
gone for vacation irl, leave the imps a note and that will be excused.  
Otherwise, if you are missing in action for more than 7 days, your imm 
will be deleted.

20) You may have your mortal on at the same time as your imm IF and only 
if you are a guild leader.  And that is for the sole purpose of keeping 
an eye on your guild.  You may not use any commands that may benefit your 
mortal, including stat, at (i.e. at <name> look).  Wiznet logins and 
attacks must be OFF, and if you decide to pk someone with your mort you 
MUST log the imm off.

21) If your mortal is online AT ALL, including Link Dead, do NOT restore 
anyone or anything.  You must log the mortal off before you do anything 
of the sort.  Otherwise it looks like you're cheating and that's BAD.

22) The IMPS (Tybalt and Chrom) are exempt to all of the above 
rules.  We've got enough common sense not to mess things up.

~
