-1 PLAYERKILL~

Playerkilling is allowed on Rivers of Blood.  However you have to follow 
the rules for it.

1) You must be level 16 to playerkill. 
2) Do not kill anyone who is under the level of 16 by any means.  This 
includes, but is not limited to...
	a) Summoning to an aggy mob
	b) Pushing an aggy mob into the room
	c) Using an area attack spell
3) You can only attack someone who is within 7 levels of your level.  For 
instance if you are level 30 you can attack a level 23 or a level 37.
4) You CANNOT attack someone who is more than 7 levels under your level 
unless they have a virtual level that is within your level range.  You 
get a virtual level by attacking someone who is more than 7 levels above 
yours.  It stays for 250 unsafe ticks, whether you die or not within that 
time.  So, you are allowed to play with the big boys... but they are also 
allowed to play with you.
5) Do NOT multikill.  This is killing someone more than once in 24 
hours.  If you kill someone you cannot attack them within that 24 hour 
time period, however if they attack you, that nulls the time period and 
you can retalliate until you kill them again.  Anything that is 
aggressive is considered an attack (charm, push, summon, etc) and if you 
are within the 24 hours of pkilling them, you cannot do any of these.
6) Do not do anything aggressive to HELPERs.
7) Do not attempt to find loopholes in these rules.  If you think it 
might be against the pkill rules, do not do it, or consult with an immortal.
~

-1 CONDUCT~
This are the rules of Rivers of Blood.  For other matters, use commom sense.

* Guild members MUST roleplay their guild.

* foul and/or abusive language will not be tolerated on RoB, from anyone
  (including gods). Punishments range from deletion to NOCHANNELing.

* sexual harassment of any form will not be tolerated, punishable by deletion

* your presence here is a privilege not a right
 
* no kill stealing from people out of level range.  This means you cannot 
  attack a mob someone else is fighting, unless they ask you to. Also 
  avoid attacking fleeing mobs.

* cheating will not be tolerated.  This includes accepting favors from gods
  and exploiting bugs. If you find a bug, report it, then do not use it.

* under no circumstances may you attack or kill your own character.  
  Period, no ands ifs or buts.  

* Everyone must be nice to newbies.  Do NOT summon them to aggy mobs,
  coerce or trick them into going into a portal where you know an aggy 
  mob is on the opposite side.  Do not make snide or rude remarks to 
  them, and offer your help to them if they are in need.  If they ask
  a question, answer it.  People that do this often and well may be
  handsomely rewarded, people that don't will be severely punished 
  (losing qp, levels, hp permanently, or slain by one of the IMPS).
  Remember you were once a newbie.  Newbies shall also be courteous
  to the higher level people.  

* No spamming.  Spamming is repeating an action repeatedly with the 
  intention to annoy.  This includes through tells, says, emotes,
  over public channels.  No one should have to go quiet in order to 
  be left alone. 

~



